        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44584",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Patch added",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-02-26T05:26:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-02-26T05:26:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44596",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm sorry, but I'm not seeing any rationale for adding this patch. Running the following:\r\n{code}\r\n$ cd tests\r\n$ phpunit Zend\/Controller\/Action\/Helper\/AllTests.php\r\n{code}\r\nruns the tests fine, with no errors of any sort.\r\n\r\nThe tests directory is added to the include_path by the PHPUnit bootstrap automatically, so the require_once statements as currently present resolve correctly.\r\n\r\nFeel free to re-open the issue if you can provide more details on why the patch is necessary (e.g., OS-specific problems).",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-01T10:12:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-01T10:12:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44602",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "bq. The tests directory is added to the include_path by the PHPUnit bootstrap automatically, so the require_once statements as currently present resolve correctly.\r\n\r\nI see... I have run tests at the wrong directory ...\r\n\r\n{code}\r\ncd tests\/Zend\/Controller\/Action\/Helper\r\nphpunit --include-path \/path\/to\/zf\/library AllTests.php\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nHowever, require_once statements are not defined consistently over test files. See for example tests\/Zend\/Controller\/Action\/AllTests.php.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kblomqvist",
                        "name": "kblomqvist",
                        "displayName": "Kim Blomqvist",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-01T10:53:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-01T10:54:04.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44604",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "We're working towards making this more consistent (ZF2 repo fixes all of this already). However, the recommended way to run tests is directly beneath the \"tests\/\" subdirectory, as we're now using a phpunit.xml file, which ensures common setup and filtering. Regardless of the inconsistencies between different AllTests.php files, this approach works across them.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2011-03-01T11:02:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2011-03-01T11:02:56.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
